    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-04-22T09:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-04-22T09:00:00-05:00" n="36"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d36">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.60i31/39: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Estonia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Carlson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tallinn</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-04-22T16:00:00+02:00"
                            >April 22, 1936—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received April 22—1:10 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>4. Referring to Department’s telegram of April 11, 3 p.m., the Foreign Office
                    handed me today a note stating principally “The Estonian Government agree to
                    withdraw their proposal as far as it concerns the expiration of the Treaty and
                    as worded in the note of the Ministry of Foreign Affairs to the American
                    Legation of May 21, 1935 (…)<note n="4a" xml:id="d36fn4a">Omission indicated in
                        the original telegram.</note>. At the same time the Estonian Government,
                    referring to the stipulations of Article 35 [<hi rend="italic">29</hi>] of the
                    existing Treaty, confirm their desire to modify the existing Treaty on May 22,
                    1937, at the latest”. Full text<note n="5" xml:id="d36fn5">Not printed.</note>
                    is being mailed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Carlson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
